assert.summary: Assertion functions, primarily for use in tests.

compare.summary: Deep or shallow object equality comparisons

cutil.summary: Functions and constructs for concurrent stratified programming

event.summary: Event emitter and utilities for dealing with events.

http.summary: Functions for performing HTTP requests and working with URLs

marked.summary: Markdown to Html Converter (tracking the [marked library](https://github.com/chjj/marked))

stream.summary: Stratified helpers for dealing with [nodejs's async streams](http://nodejs.org/api/stream.html)

numeric.summary: Functions for numeric linear algebra computations from [numericjs.com](http://numericjs.com)

observable.summary: Constructs for manipulating streams backed by time-varying values

regexp.summary: Functions for working with regular expressions

sequence.summary: Constructs for manipulating sequence structures (arrays, strings and more general streams)

sjcl.summary: Stanford JavaScript Crypto Library from http://crypto.stanford.edu/sjcl/

reporter.summary: Reporter objects for outputting test suite results

dom-shim.summary: DOM polyfills for non-conformant browsers (IE8, IE9)

html2canvas.summary: Generate virtual screenshots of HTML elements (tracking the [html2canvas library](http://html2canvas.hertzen.com/))

summary: Standard collection of modules for the StratifiedJS language
